from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
from typing import Any

class BaseEDAAgent(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def act(self, input_data: Any) -> Any:
        """Main task of the agent"""
        pass

    def respond(self, feedback: Any = None) -> Any:
        """Optional feedback loop for iterative improvements"""
        return None

    All child agents inherit BaseEDAAgent:

class DataPrepAgent(BaseEDAAgent):
    def act(self, input_data):
        # Load & clean data
        return cleaned_data

    Benefits:

        Parent AssistantAgent can call act() on any child agent without knowing the exact implementation.

        Later, switching to async execution is as simple as wrapping act() in async def calls.

        Swarm/GroupChat-ready: the parent can distribute tasks to multiple agents in parallel using the same interface.

Summary

    Hierarchical Pattern: centralized orchestrator, children communicate only through parent.

    Standard interface (ABC): ensures all agents are modular, interchangeable, and future-proof for async or Swarm expansion.

